# Agent bootstrap (SSOT)

1. **Primary** — Work from the **master canvas** (see [MASTER_PROGRAM_CANVAS_COMPANION_2026-04-27.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/MASTER_PROGRAM_CANVAS_COMPANION_2026-04-27.md)), [docs/00_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/00_SSOT.md) (**Agent task routing** picks parent SSOTs per task—avoid loading every doc), [STANDARDS_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/STANDARDS_SSOT.md), and [AGENTS.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/AGENTS.md). **Cursor/Grok hierarchy + autonomous loops:** [cursor-grok-agent-hierarchy-and-loops.mdc](cursor-grok-agent-hierarchy-and-loops.mdc) + [CURSOR_GROK_AGENT_HIERARCHY_AND_LOOP_OPTIMIZATION_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_GROK_AGENT_HIERARCHY_AND_LOOP_OPTIMIZATION_SSOT.md) + [CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_AUTONOMOUS_LOOP_AND_PR_WORKFLOW_SSOT.md). **Cross-host Cursor (M5 ↔ RHEL):** [cursor-cross-host-enforcement-sync.mdc](cursor-cross-host-enforcement-sync.mdc) + [CURSOR_CROSS_HOST_SYNC_PROTOCOL_2026-04-27.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CURSOR_CROSS_HOST_SYNC_PROTOCOL_2026-04-27.md). Full local verify matrix: [CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md) **§3** (do not duplicate script lists in chat). **Automation contract:** [NEW_CHAT_SINGLE_FILE_HANDOFF_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/NEW_CHAT_SINGLE_FILE_HANDOFF_SSOT.md) **§0** — default **`OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN`** / **`credential-manager`** / platform stores per [ONEPASSWORD_CLI_SESSION_GATE_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/ONEPASSWORD_CLI_SESSION_GATE_SSOT.md) **§3.1**; human **only** for interactive **§1** **`op`** when **no** unattended path exists in **that** shell, **Cloudflare token mint**, **ADR**-level policy exceptions, or **named vault field** gaps (**MISS** in diagnostics)—not vague “fix **`op`**.” Use **Integrated Terminal** + `lib-load-cf-deploy-token.sh` / Keychain / service account for deploy and verification before asking the operator for anything else. **On workspace open:** [`.cursor/hooks.json`](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/.cursor/hooks.json) **`sessionStart`** runs **`scripts/cursor-session-start-automation.sh`** (P0 **`GET /health`** ping → **`.cursor/hooks/logs/session-start-automation.log`**). **When shells misbehave:** [OPERATOR_SESSION_START_AND_IDE_REALITY_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/OPERATOR_SESSION_START_AND_IDE_REALITY_SSOT.md) + [CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CONTINUE_ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK_SSOT.md) **§0.4**. **macOS privacy:** system **“access data from other apps”** prompts name the **third-party TCC requester** (e.g. a browser)—**§B** — not **`cursor-security-watch`** / `.cursor/` misconfig by default; [STANDARDS_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/STANDARDS_SSOT.md) **Trusted macOS workstation — Apple TCC**. This governs all projects and **does not** require the repo **mentor** subagent.

**Gate / policy authority (2026-05-25 fleet audit formalization — mandatory "if ANY question" reference)**: See the authoritative [CLOUDFLARE_SECURITY_CONTROLS_MATRIX_AND_GAPS_SSOT.md §4a.4.0 "Program Gate Definition — Single Source of Truth"](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CLOUDFLARE_SECURITY_CONTROLS_MATRIX_AND_GAPS_SSOT.md#4a40-program-gate-definition-single-source-of-truth) (two-layer 80%/95% model + Master Cross-Domain Gate Table + 18-item pre-boarding checklist; full 2026-05-25 decisions: ADR-0027/0028 staged, G30 FIPS (O.2 PG-1="FedRAMP-path"), O.2 PG deliberately paused for boarding+quality/ADR focus (resumption only under ADR-0031+G30+G37+§4a.4.0 gate), doc-driven/ADR/wiki shift as primary quality mechanism, local red/blue/purple+CI fallback). All gate/ADR/quality/boarding claims governed here. Evidence in FLEET_AUDIT_GAP_REGISTER_2026-05-25.md + COMPREHENSIVE + CONTINUE_PLAYBOOK. (Full formal in audit report §3.) This is the "if ANY question" contract per the 2026-05-25 Fleet Representation Audit. Same-change-set discipline applies. (Agent bootstrap must surface this for all cold starts.)
2. **Optional** — The only custom subagent is **`/ssot-program-mentor`**: for English-only help using `/` in chat, or a quick alignment check with program objectives (security, doc sprawl, reuse, TS→Rust). Suggest it **only** if the user asks about subagents, is confused, or is experimenting with `/`; do **not** add standing “subagent prompt” blocks every turn.
3. **Vendor docs before Cloudflare or xAI work** — [vendor-documentation-first-cloudflare-xai.mdc](vendor-documentation-first-cloudflare-xai.mdc) + [docs/VENDOR_DOCUMENTATION_FIRST_CLOUDFLARE_XAI_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/VENDOR_DOCUMENTATION_FIRST_CLOUDFLARE_XAI_SSOT.md) (official MCP / vendor URLs; not model memory alone).
4. All substantive Cloudflare, workflow, and verification work happens in **normal agent chat** with the existing rules (e.g. [agent-cloudflare-execution.mdc](agent-cloudflare-execution.mdc), [devsecops-enforcement.mdc](devsecops-enforcement.mdc)).
5. **Hooks / guard** — do not suggest bypassing [`.cursor/hooks.json`](.cursor/hooks.json) or mutating Cloudflare without [scripts/cloudflare-guard-preflight.sh](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/scripts/cloudflare-guard-preflight.sh) when policy requires it.
6. **Rust-first (program automation + Workers)** — [rust-first-program-automation.mdc](rust-first-program-automation.mdc) + [rust-edge-workers-preference.mdc](rust-edge-workers-preference.mdc); canonical prose [STANDARDS_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/STANDARDS_SSOT.md) Language Strategy (**program automation** bullet). New orchestration belongs in **`crates/`** (for example **`background-prompt-sweep`**), not new Python runners.
